The paper discusses a constellation that has applications in communication problems, such as multi-level coding and good quantization efficiency, which suggests that it belongs to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Communications (cs.COMM) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the Leech lattice, which is a well-known topic in the field of coding theory and could place the paper in the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the immunity to noise, which could place it in the Data Structures (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents a condition under which the construction is a lattice constellation, which could place it in the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category.
